---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'About ssdicalc.com';
const description = 'About the team behind ssdicalc.com — free SSDI benefit calculators and plain-English Social Security disability guides.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <h1>About ssdicalc.com</h1>

  <p>ssdicalc.com is a free Social Security disability resource maintained by The Click Lab. Our SSDI benefit calculator applies SSA&rsquo;s official Primary Insurance Amount formula directly to your estimated earnings, producing a monthly benefit estimate that reflects how the program actually works &mdash; not a simplified approximation. Our guide library covers eligibility rules, the application and appeals process, the SSDI vs. SSI distinction, and common misconceptions that cause applicants to make costly procedural mistakes.</p>

  <h2>What we do</h2>
  <p>We translate SSA&rsquo;s technical program rules &mdash; bend points, work credit requirements, the five-step sequential evaluation, trial work period mechanics &mdash; into plain language that a person who has just received a disabling diagnosis can actually use. Every page is written and reviewed against primary SSA sources (the Social Security Act, POMS, SSA statistical publications) before publication and updated when benefit thresholds or program rules change.</p>
  <p>Our <a href="/methodology">methodology page</a> documents the calculator formula in full. We aim to be the most transparent free SSDI resource available &mdash; you should always be able to trace a number on this site back to the SSA source it came from.</p>

  <h2>What we don&rsquo;t do</h2>
  <p>We do not provide legal advice or predict individual case outcomes. SSDI eligibility involves a complex administrative evaluation of your specific medical record and work history that no calculator or general guide can replicate. For guidance on your own claim, consult a licensed disability attorney or SSA-accredited representative. Most work on contingency with no upfront fee.</p>
  <p>We do not recommend specific law firms, earn referral fees from disability attorney directories, or accept sponsored content. Editorial decisions are independent of advertising relationships.</p>

  <h2>How we make money</h2>
  <p>ssdicalc.com is supported by Google AdSense display advertising. We do not sell reader data or share visitor information for advertising targeting beyond what Google&rsquo;s standard AdSense program involves. See our <a href="/privacy">privacy policy</a> for full details.</p>

  <h2>Who maintains this site</h2>
  <p>ssdicalc.com is owned and operated by The Click Lab. The editorial team is led by Faye Underwood, Editor-in-Chief for Social Security Disability Practice, with contributing research from Bart Crenshaw. More information about the team and editorial process is on the <a href="/editorial">editorial page</a>.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Questions, corrections, or feedback: see our <a href="/contact">contact page</a>. We read every message. We cannot respond to requests for legal advice, case-specific analysis, or attorney referrals.</p>
</BaseLayout>
